11 An Act relating to public health and safety; amending
63 O.S. 2021, Section 2-1101, which relates to harm-
12 reduction services; deleting sunset date; and
providing an effective date.
13
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 63 O.S. 2021, Section 2-1101, is
17 amended to read as follows:
18 Section 2-1101. A. Until July 1, 2026 2031, the following are
19 hereby authorized to engage in harm-reduction services:
20 1. Government entities including, but not limited to, the State
21 Department of Health and the Department of Mental Health and
22 Substance Abuse Services; provided, no state dollars shall be used
23 to purchase hypodermic needles;
24 2. Religious institutions or churches;
HB2012 HFLR Page 1
